Penetration test 

By modifying the PTAN in the POST request variables, a user could access other user's data via the Dashboard.
The UserID was sent as an HTTP Header.  This could easily be changed to a different UserID to potentially access other account data.


The application restricted file uploads to certain file types.  This could be bypassed by modifying the POST request file name and file contents to send a restricted file type.

Verbose SQL Error in HTTP Response Header

A duplicate session ID in the POST request parameters caused the application to respond with a verbose SQL error in the HTTP response header.



